Here is an example of how to generate a table of contents (TOC) automatically in a LaTeX document using the `\tableofcontents` command:
```
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\section{Section 1}
\subsection{Subsection 1.1}
\subsection{Subsection 1.2}

\section{Section 2}
\subsection{Subsection 2.1}
\subsection{Subsection 2.2}

\section*{Appendix}
\subsection*{Appendix subsection}

\end{document}
```
The `\tableofcontents` command is used to generate the TOC. It should be placed where you want the TOC to appear in your document, usually at the beginning.

